<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,691,717]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
Prior to its recognition as a distinct species, several studies (see cresonymy above) had already recorded 
<taxonomicName box="[234,483,727,753]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Leptophis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dibernardoi">
<emphasis box="[234,483,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Leptophis dibernardoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Oliver" authorityYear="1942" box="[519,654,727,753]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Leptophis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ahaetulla">
